Loadshedding has been been reduced to stage 3. Eskom announced that this will kick in at 10pm on Wednesday. The power utility said that six generation units have returned to service in the last 24 hours and that loadshedding stage 3 will continue until Friday. Earlier today, CEO André De Ruyter, assured citizens that a total blackout was not on the cards. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.